elements.description:
`saved-panel-list`

## Styling

`<saved-panel-list>` provides the following custom properties and mixins for styling:

Custom property | Description | Default
----------------|-------------|----------
`--saved-panel-list` | Mixin applied to this elment | `{}`
`--saved-panel-list-url-label` | Mixin applied to the list container | `{}`
`--saved-panel-list-secondary-action-color` | Color of the secondary action button | `--primary-color`
`--saved-panel-list-url-label` | Mixin applied to the URL label | `{}`
`--saved-panel-list-method-label` | Mixin applied to the method label | `{}`

properties.name: threshold
properties.description:
A list lower treshold when the `history-list-threshold` will be
fired. It should informa the app that the user nearly reached
the end of the list and new items should be loaded.

properties.name: _scrollTarget
properties.description:
Scroll target for `iron-scroll-threshold`.
This is set in connectedCallback as the DOM has to be initialized
before setting this property.

properties.name: selectedItems
properties.description: List of selected items on the list.

properties.name: hasTwoLines
properties.description: When set the list items are rendered having 2 lines.

properties.name: draggableEnabled
properties.description:
Adds draggable property to the request list item element.
The `dataTransfer` object has `arc/request-object` mime type with
serialized JSON with request model.

methods.name: notifyResize
methods.description:
Notifies the list that the resize event occurred.
Should be called whhen content of the list changed but the list wasn't
visible at the time.

methods.name: _computeRowClass
methods.description: Computes list item row class

params.name: selected
params.description: True if the item was selected

return.desc: Item class name dependeing on selection state

methods.name: _dragStart
methods.description:
Handler for the `dragstart` event added to the list item when `draggableEnabled`
is set to true.
This function sets request data on the `dataTransfer` object with `arc/request-object`
mime type. The request data is a serialized JSON with request model.

methods.name: _computeDraggableValue
methods.description:
Computes value for the `draggable` property of the list item.
When `draggableEnabled` is set it returns true which is one of the
conditions to enable drag and drop on an element.

return.desc: `true` or `false` (as string) depending on the argument.

methods.name: _dragoverHandler
methods.description:
Handler for `dragover` event on this element. If the dagged item is compatible
it renders drop message.

methods.name: _dragleaveHandler
methods.description:
Handler for `dragleave` event on this element. If the dagged item is compatible
it hides drop message.

methods.name: _dropHandler
methods.description:
Handler for `drag` event on this element. If the dagged item is compatible
it adds request to saved requests.

methods.name: _appendRequest
methods.description:
Dispatches (by calling `_dispatch() function`) `save-request` event
which is handled by request model to create new request.
The function do not need to do anything else since request change listeners
will insert the request to the list when saved.

elements.description:
Saved requests panel for ARC.

Contains complete UI to support saved requests view.

### Styling

`<saved-requests-panel>` provides the following custom properties and mixins for styling:

Custom property | Description | Default
----------------|-------------|----------
`--warning-primary-color` | Main color of the warning messages | `#FF7043`
`--warning-contrast-color` | Contrast color for the warning color | `#fff`
`--saved-requests-panel-fab-background-color` | Color of the fab button in the details panel | `--primary-color`
`--context-menu-item-color` | Color of the dropdown menu items | ``
`--context-menu-item-background-color` | Background olor of the dropdown menu items | ``
`--context-menu-item-color-hover` | Color of the dropdown menu items when hovering | ``
`--context-menu-item-background-color-hover` | Background olor of the dropdown menu items when hovering | ``

properties.name: _latestDeleted
properties.description: List of requests that has been recently removed

properties.name: listHidden
properties.description: Computed value, true if the requests lists is hidden.

properties.name: hasSelection
properties.description: Computed value, true when the user made a selection on the list.

properties.name: editorOpened
properties.description: When true the editor panel is rendered

properties.name: detailsOpened
properties.description: When true the details panel is rendered

properties.name: selectedProjects
properties.description: List of selected in the dialog project names.

properties.name: draggableEnabled
properties.description: Enables the comonent to accept drop action with a request.

properties.name: _exportOptionsOpened
properties.description: Indicates that the export options panel is currently rendered.

methods.name: notifyResize
methods.description:
Notifies the list that the resize event occurred.
Should be called whhen content of the list changed but the list wasn't
visible at the time.

methods.name: _computeListHidden
methods.description:
Computes value of the `listHidden` property.
List is hidden when no requests are found and it is not searching.

methods.name: _navigateHandler
methods.description: Handler for navigate action from the list

methods.name: _onDetails
methods.description: Opens the request details applet with the request.

methods.name: _loadRequestDetails
methods.description: Fires `navigate` event for currently loaded in the details request.

methods.name: _searchHandler
methods.description: Handler for search event from search input.

methods.name: _deleteSelected
methods.description: Handles items delete event from item click.

methods.name: _deleteRequestDetails
methods.description: Deletes a request from the details panel.

methods.name: _delete
methods.description: Performs a delete action of request items.

methods.name: _dispatchDelete
methods.description: Dispatches `request-objects-deleted` event.

methods.name: revertDeleted
methods.description:
Restores removed requests.
It does nothing if `_latestDeleted` is not set or empty.

return.desc: A promise resolved when objects were restored

methods.name: _dispatchUndelete
methods.description: Dispatches `request-objects-undeleted` event.

params.name: items
params.description:
List of deleted requests. The list
contains objects with `_id` and `_rev` properties.

methods.name: _closeSelectionMenu
methods.description: Forces selection menu to close.

methods.name: _closeMainMenu
methods.description: Forces main menu to close.

methods.name: openExportAll
methods.description: Toggles export options panel and sets export items to all currently loaded requests.

methods.name: _exportAllFile
methods.description: Creates export file for all items.

methods.name: _doExportItems
methods.description:
Calls `_dispatchExportData()` from requests lists mixin with
prepared arguments

params.name: requests
params.description: List of request to export with the project.

methods.name: _deleteAllClick
methods.description: Handler for delete all menu option click.

methods.name: _onClearDialogResult
methods.description: Called when delete datastore dialog is closed.

methods.name: _clearDatastore
methods.description: Removes all data from the datastore and then fires

methods.name: _dispatchDeleteModel
methods.description: Dispatches `destroy-model` with `saved` on the models list.

methods.name: _editRequestDetails
methods.description: Opens request details editor in place of the request details applet.

methods.name: _saveRequestEdit
methods.description: Handler to save the request event from the editor.

methods.name: _computeA11yCommand
methods.description: Computes a proper key command depending on the platform.

params.name: key
params.description: The key modifier for the command

methods.name: _projectSelected
methods.description: Handles menu click for adding selected requests to a project.

methods.name: cancelAddProject
methods.description: Cancels adding to project dialog.

methods.name: _updateRequestsProjects
methods.description: Updates requests objects with projects ids.

methods.name: _addSelectedProject
methods.description: Adds selected requests to a project.

methods.name: _createProjects
methods.description:
Dispatches `project-update-bulk` custom event and returns event's
promise.

params.name: requestIds
params.description: List of request IDs to associate with the project.

methods.name: _updateListStyles
methods.description:
Updates icon size CSS variable and notifies resize on the list when
list type changes.

methods.name: _projectAddKeydown
methods.description: Listens for Enter + cmd/ctrl button to accept project selection.
